##Waiting for spring in the spring

Wechat, bingdianweekly

Features, China Youth Daily's in depth reporting brand. We believe that news has more than one day of life.

Slaughterhouse Buys Li Jifa's geese

About 2,952 words

Estimated Reading Time: 8 minutes

Author | Zhongqingbao Zhongqingwang Trainee Reporter, Yin Haiyue

Editor | Chen Zhuo

500 ducks were saved. After 10 days without food, Liu Xiaohong, a farmer in Yichang, Hubei Province, finally got a temporary pass issued by the village on Feb. 11. He contacted the county's yet-to-be-opened feed distributor and bought 2,000 catties of feed to save his last remaining ducks.

He had 2,000 ducks. But he, like many farmers across the country, can not buy feed because of a new outbreak of pneumonia. At that time, Liu Xiaohong woke up every morning to see a duck shed east, west a lying dead ducks, a day at least more than 100, at most several hundred dead ducks. Now, this spring, he begins to plan for the 500 ducks.

For many farmers, the Spring Festival is an important time. Each year around the Spring Festival is the peak of live poultry trade, many farmers will choose to sell poultry during this period, and then the following spring to invest in a new round of breeding.

The spring came after a long winter. Under the cover of the epidemic, some chicken seedling hatchery plant buried a batch of seedlings alive, but also some farmers will be unsalable poultry thrown into the pit of soil, many people in this cold winter "one night back before Liberation" , several years of rapid accumulation of funds cleared, or even face debt. They must find a way to get through the spring.

1

The News of spring came in succession. On February 15, the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas and other three departments issued a circular calling for the resumption of production in the aquaculture industry. In addition to Wuhan and other severely affected cities, the temporary closure of highways around the beginning of the recovery, has been cut off the rural road is gradually unimpeded.

When Liu Xiaohong got her temporary pass to pull up the feed on February 11, four or five kilometers of road had to pass through at least 10 intersections, and every intersection had to be stopped for inspection. Liu Xiaohong saw that the streets were empty, and in order to prevent people from going out, there are only red lights at every intersection.

Even so, this is good news. His ducks went without food on February 1st, and then a neighbor's fields of vegetables helped him through a difficult time —— because the roads were closed and the vegetables were rotting in the fields, and Liu drove a tricycle every day, to chop vegetables and bring them back to feed the ducks.

Unable to feed the 2,000 ducks on vegetables alone, he fished in a neighbour's pond -- until the fish died as a result of the outbreak.

After 10 hard days, he finally waited for the road block to thaw bit by bit.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Liu Xiaohong from the next door to the unsalable fish feeding ducks

But not all farmers have been able to successfully wait until this day. Zhu Bin, a farmer in Huanggang, Hubei Province, raises more than 10,000 chickens, which consume 5,000 to 6,000 yuan of feed a day. Since the outbreak, Zhu bin every day in the progress of the epidemic, to see the daily increase in confirmed cases, Zhu has been asking the Slaughterhouse Start Date, the results are constantly delayed.

This let Zhu bin feel, "in a month after definitely no hope. " Measure, Zhu bin decided to bury the chicken. More than 10,000 live chickens were bagged and dumped into pits, where disinfectant water and lime were poured, and the birds'lives were cut short by the fall of the excavator. Zhu Bin became one of the first farmers to bury chickens.

Another 90,000 chickens belonging to Hubei Huanggang farmer Liu Chuanhou were also buried on the 15th day of the first lunar month. He estimated the loss to be more than 1 million yuan, years of accumulation in vain, "all lost. "

Farmers are not the only ones who have been affected. Traffic and transportation have been blocked because of the closure of live poultry trade. Chicks (chicks that have just come out of the Shell) can not be transported to farms. Many hatcheries have had to bury the chicks that hatched during the outbreak. Wang Renrui, a general agent for the Poultry Research Institute of the Chinese Academy of Agricultural Sciences in Yangzhou, Jiangsu, told reporters that because the chickens could not be transported from Jiangsu to Hunan, the 300,000 chicks ordered from the institute in the first month of the year in Hunan Province were also buried.

A source from a chicken FRY hatchery in Guangzhou told the reporter that the sales of Guangdong chicken fry in the first month were concentrated between the sixth day and the 20th day of the first month. During this period, about two-thirds of the chicken fry in the whole province were disposed of because they could not reach the farm. The director told reporters that due to concerns about the continuation of the epidemic, some incubators have taken certain emergency measures to delay the hatching time of chicken seedlings.

At the end of February, Guangdong, Jiangxi, Anhui, Gansu and other places issued a paper calling for the gradual opening of the live poultry market. As the supply of hatcheries decreased in the short term, farmers'demand for chicks rose, and the prices of chicks rose everywhere. "The lowest 1.60 is now 2.10,2.20. The price of our chicken seedlings used to be 4.80 yuan, but now it's up to 5.50 yuan,"Chen Yucong, a farmer in Xiangtan, Hunan, who ordered chicken seedlings for poultry research at the Chinese Academy of Agricultural Sciences, told reporters.

The rise in the price of chicken seedlings has further increased the cost of raising farmers. However, the Chinese Academy of Agricultural Sciences Institute of poultry prices have been stable, Chen Yucong unaffected by the market. But for Chen, the delayed arrival of the day's young chicks means a delay in production plans for the year, which means they won't be able to catch the peak price of eggs on the Dragon Boat Festival and sell them in time for the 2021.

2

Before the outbreak, many people had high hopes for this spring.

Liu Xiaohong's ducks had just begun to lay eggs. Liu Xiaohong has been engaged in breeding for six or seven years. Laying ducks are raised for a long time and are in no hurry to sell. He makes a profit by selling eggs. At the end of 2019, the ducks finally began laying eggs. Although the temperature was low and the amount of eggs produced was small, Liu Xiaohong was very happy. He gave all 300 eggs to relatives and friends. After waiting for the Spring Festival, the ducks slowly increased their egg production and concentrated their sales.

"At the time, I felt I could finally start paying back my investment. " Liu Xiaohong estimated from her heart how much money she could earn. According to the lowest prices, a duck egg could earn 0.25 yuan, and at a daily 90 percent egg-laying rate, 1,800 eggs could earn 450 yuan a day, i make over $10,000 a month.

"I used to be a part-time worker, so I thought it would be OK, " Ms. Liu said.

Chen Songtao, a villager from Liu Meng village, Shangqiao town, Luohe City, Henan Province, is also looking forward to the upcoming Spring Festival. In the past, Chen also worked outside the home. In 2017, he contracted uremia and had to go to the hospital twice a day for dialysis. Without a source of income, he became a poor household in the village.

To make ends meet, in 2019, Chen borrowed 25,000 yuan from the village and two hundred thousand from relatives to buy 4,000 chicks from Guangxi. He plans to sell more than 3,000 birds on the 15th day of the first lunar month, hoping to make at least 10,000 yuan.

The arrival of the epidemic shattered expectations. On the eighth day of the first lunar month, Chen Songtao wants to enter the feed, but can not go out the door.

By February 24, Chen had only half a ton of feed left. Because there was no money to buy feed, Chen only fed the chickens once a day. At night, he would turn off the lights in the chicken coop and the chickens would lie still. But at first light, the chickens are still hungry.

He had to find a way to sell the chickens. It started with friends and family. The main road in the village was blocked. When someone bought it, he went to find a dirt road to make a delivery.

Later, village and township cadres began to help Chen Songtao sell chickens, but also put the matter in the "Luohe daily. ". On March 2, Chen's chicken was sold out.

For farmers, every day that poultry is out of stock means another day of lost costs.

In Shangqiu, Li Jifa's 3,000 geese, which were released around the 10th day of the first lunar month, are also facing slow sales. More than 3,000 goose daily consumption of 2,000 yuan of feed, "you do not sell, a day will lose 2,000 yuan. "

On February 26, he waited for a truck from the slaughterhouse. However, due to the high transportation cost and the large amount of geese sold, Li Jifa's more than 3,000 geese were ultimately sold for 5 yuan more than a Jin, "This time last year the price of goose was about 9 yuan, " which cost Li Jifa about 100,000 yuan.

The shortage of fund chain is the most urgent problem that most farmers are facing at present. After burying 90,000 chickens, Liu Chuanhou is looking for ways to get an interest-free loan as he ponders how to raise start-up capital as soon as possible this spring.

Farming will continue. Zhu Bin plans to release the seal before entering the seedlings. The sudden drop of the crisis also did not let Liu Xiaohong on breeding lost confidence, in the duck "food rations" for twenty days, Liu Xiaohong once depressed, "I think this is not good, that is not good. "

Liu raised pigs last year, catching up with the 2019 swine fever, 200 pigs sold 20, the rest were all sick buried alive, loss of three hundred thousand. "At that time I felt that the disease was too severe and I dared not feed the pigs again. " Liu Xiaohong then turned to raising ducks and thought of feeding the pigs for two years.

The outbreak has dashed his hopes once again. "still inferior with elder brother a few work to go. " Liu Xiaogong when a person quiets down to think, always feel in the mind is afflictive. In a twinkling of an eye, but also feel that there is no fun to work, he constantly give himself to do psychological construction, to cheer up, "where the fall, where the rise. "

A few years grope down, Liu Xiaohong thinks still raise a pig a few simple, benefit also than raise a duck tall. By the end of 2019, he had restocked 40 pigs, which ate little and were not bothered by feed problems.

After the epidemic, Liu Xiaohong decided to sell all the ducks, concentrate on raising pigs. He planned to sell the pigs for the Dragon Boat Festival and bring in new piglets.

Now, Liu Xiaohong is the most happy thing every day is to feed the pig, watching a herd of pigs, Sahuan son issued a cry, Liu Xiaohong mood also followed up. The 40 pigs in front of him are all he hopes for 2020.
